Context:
The School of Liberal Arts and Sciences at George Brown College offers regular information sessions for the General Arts and Science One-Year Certificate (R104) and the General Arts and Science Two-Year Diploma (R101). These sessions provide an opportunity to have questions answered, learn about program content and career options, meet professors and staff, and experience college classrooms. Interested individuals can sign up to be kept informed about application deadlines, college news, upcoming events, tours, and more.

Contact information:
- Phone: 416-415-2000
- TTY: 1-877-515-5559
- Email: ask.george@georgebrown.ca

Website note: The information contained in the website is subject to change without notice and should not be considered as a representation, offer, or warranty. Students are responsible for verifying George Brown College fee requirements.
